## 5. Deploying the Week 3 Docker App on EC2

With Docker installed, we pulled the app from GitHub and ran it on the server.

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/devops-internship-labs.git

# Go to the Week 3 app directory
cd devops-internship-labs/week3/docker-app

# Build the image
docker build -t devops-web-cloud:v1 .

# Run the container, expose port 80
docker run -d --name devops-web-cloud -p 80:80 devops-web-cloud:v1

# Verify it's running
docker ps

# Check logs
docker logs devops-web-cloud
```

Then from a local browser:

```
http://YOUR_EC2_PUBLIC_IP
```

**How it works end-to-end:**
1. Docker builds the image from the `Dockerfile` in the repo
2. The container starts and listens on port 80 inside the container
3. `-p 80:80` maps EC2's port 80 to the container's port 80
4. The security group allows traffic on port 80 from the internet
5. Browser hits the public IP on port 80, reaches the container, gets the response

<!-- Screenshot: docker ps showing devops-web-cloud running -->
![Docker Container Running](./screenshots/docker-ps-ec2.png)

<!-- Screenshot: Browser showing the app at EC2 public IP -->
